What an honor to meet with Salvador Barajas and recognize him as our Constituent of the Month. 

Salvador is an outstanding historical muralist and visionary artist who was one of the first artists to create murals in Chicano Park. Since then, he has been a driving force in the creation, restoration, and preservation of Chicano Park murals. 

Additionally, Salvador is the founder of Motivational Design and has completed more than 500 public art projects throughout Southern California. 

Salvador's art has inspired our community and will empower generations to come. Thank you, Salvador, for all you do!

Today, I join the world in mourning the passing of Pope Francis. As the first Jesuit and first Latin American pope, his tenure broke barriers. He defended the dignity of all people, dedicated himself to justice, and uplifted the most vulnerable and marginalized in our communities.
